<section id="running-examples" class="title-slide slide level2 center">
<h2>Running Examples</h2>
<p>We’ll use two microbiota “collated” datasets:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>One vaginal microbiota dataset: The ISALA dataset [add ref] <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span></p></li>
<li><p>One gut microbiota dataset: <code>curatedMetagenomics</code> [add ref] <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span></p></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="vaginal-microbiota-dataset-valencia" class="slide level3">
<h3>Vaginal microbiota dataset: Valencia</h3>
<p>Valencia is a vaginal microbiota “classifier” (more on this later) developed by Michael France (Ravel’s lab).</p>
<div class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center">
<figure>
<p><img data-src="images/Valencia.png" width="400"></p>
</figure>
</div>
<p><span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> Add reference</p>
<p>https://github.com/ravel-lab/VALENCIA</p>
<p>https://microbiomejournal.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s40168-020-00934-6</p>
<p>France, M.T., Ma, B., Gajer, P. et al.&nbsp;VALENCIA: a nearest centroid classification method for vaginal microbial communities based on composition. Microbiome 8, 166 (2020). https://doi.org/10.1186/s40168-020-00934-6</p>
<div class="fragment">
<p>To build their classifier, they also curated a large dataset of microbiota samples from several cohorts.</p>
<p>This data is available on Valencia’s GitHub repository as <code>csv</code> files.</p>
<p><span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> Add link</p>
<div class="cell" data-hash="LDA-for-microbiota_cache/revealjs/unnamed-chunk-2_7590a4f49a5930549f597e85e49311ab">
<details>
<summary>Code</summary>
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb2"><pre class="sourceCode numberSource r number-lines code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1"></a>valencia_counts_raw <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">read_csv</span>(<span class="at">file =</span> <span class="st">"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ravel-lab/VALENCIA/refs/heads/master/Publication_materials/Data_and_metadata/all_samples_taxonomic_composition_data.csv"</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2"></a>valencia_metadata_raw <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">read_csv</span>(<span class="at">file =</span> <span class="st">"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ravel-lab/VALENCIA/refs/heads/master/Publication_materials/Data_and_metadata/all_samples_metadata.csv"</span>)</span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</details>
</div>
<p>After some formating (creation of a <code>SummarizedExperiment</code> object), we can use this data.</p>
