</div>
<div class="agenda-inactive agenda-post-active">
<p>test</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="what-are-topic-models" class="title-slide slide level2 center">
<h2>What are topic models?</h2>
<div class="fragment">
<p>They are statistical models for identifying “<em>topics</em>” in corpus of text documents.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section id="topic-models-1" class="slide level3">
<h3>Topic models</h3>
<p><span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> -&gt; Illustration</p>
</section>
<section id="topic-models-2" class="slide level3">
<h3>Topic models</h3>
<p>Several Bayesian and non-Bayesian models have been proposed:</p>
<ul>
<li>Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> add refs</li>
<li>and derived models (<em>e.g.</em>, Hierarchical LDA) <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> add refs</li>
<li>Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF) <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> add refs</li>
<li>(p)LSA/LSI (Latent Semantic Analysis/Indexing) <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> add refs</li>
<li>…</li>
</ul>
<div class="fragment">
<ul>
<li>There are also “supervised” versions of topic models (<em>e.g.</em>, <span class="emoji" data-emoji="warning">⚠️</span> add refs)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
<section id="lda" class="slide level3">
<h3>LDA</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>Plate diagram</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Generative model</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Inference</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><code>R</code> implementations: <code>topicmodels</code> package</p>
</blockquote>
</section>

<section id="lda-for-microbiota-data" class="title-slide slide level2 center">
<h2>LDA for microbiota data?</h2>

</section>
<section id="lda-for-microbiota-data-1" class="slide level3">
<h3>LDA for microbiota data</h3>
<table>
<caption>warning: add illustration</caption>
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th>NLP</th>
<th>Microbiota analyses</th>
</tr>
